olive oil
2 Potato
1 packet Thyme
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 packet Sirloin Steak
1 Orange
1 Cucumber
1 packet Rocket leaves
1 packet balsamic glaze
1 packet Garlic Aioli

• See ‘Top Steak Tips!’ (below).
• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Pick and finely chop thyme.
• Place potato and thyme on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast slivered almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes.

• Wipe out and return large frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook sirloin steak for 5-6 minutes each side for medium, or until cooked to your liking.
• Using tongs, hold steak upright and sear fat until golden, 1 minute.
• Remove steak from pan and rest for 5 minutes. Season with salt.

TIP: The meat will keep cooking as it rests!

• Meanwhile, peel and thinly slice orange into wedges.
• Thinly slice cucumber into rounds.
• In a large bowl, combine orange, cucumber, rocket leaves and balsamic glaze. Season to taste.

• Thinly slice steak.
• Divide sirloin steak, herby potatoes and orange and rocket salad
between plates.
• Sprinkle almonds over salad.
• Dollop with garlic aioli to serve. Enjoy!